data: {"content": "\n\nHere is a proposed structure for your one-time pre-purchase inspection checklist of a 2012 Daewoo Lacetti. Please review and let me know if you\u2019d like any changes. Once you confirm, I will generate the final checklist.\n\n## Engine & Cooling System\n1. Check engine oil level and dipstick reading [number]  \n2. Assess engine oil color/condition [longText]  \n3. Engine oil leaks visible? [list]  \n4. Coolant level and fill concentration [list]  \n5. Coolant color and contamination (rust/debris) [longText]  \n6. Coolant hoses/crimps condition (soft spots, cracks) [list]  \n7. Radiator core and cap condition [list]  \n8. Inspect drive belts (serpentine, timing) for wear/tension [list]  \n\n## Transmission & Drivetrain\n1. Transmission fluid level and condition [list]  \n2. Fluid color (clear/red/burnt) and odor [longText]  \n3. Transmission leaks (seal/pan) [list]  \n4. Clutch engagement (manual) or shift quality (auto) [longText]  \n5. CV joint boots and axle shafts condition [list]  \n6. Differential fluid level and leaks [list]  \n\n## Brakes & Parking Brake\n1. Front brake pad thickness (mm) [number]  \n2. Rear brake pad thickness (mm) [number]  \n3. Brake disc/rotor condition (scoring, thickness) [list]  \n4. Brake fluid level and clarity [list]  \n5. Brake fluid age/mileage since change [textAnswer]  \n6. Brake hoses/lines for cracks or swelling [list]  \n7. Parking brake operation and tension [list]  \n\n## Suspension & Steering\n1. Shock absorber/strut leaks or damage [list]  \n2. Ball joints, tie rods, control arms play [list]  \n3. Power steering fluid level and leaks [list]  \n4. Steering rack boots condition [list]  \n5. Test steering effort, play, noise [longText]  \n\n## Wheels & Tires\n1. Tire tread depth (mm) each corner [number]  \n2. Tire sidewall damage or bulges [list]  \n3. Tire pressure each tire (psi) [number]  \n4. Wheel rim condition (bends, corrosion) [list]  \n5. Spare tire condition and pressure [list]  \n\n## Body & Exterior\n1. Inspect body panels for rust, dents, paint mismatch [list]  \n2. Door, hood, trunk alignment and gaps [list]  \n3. Window and windshield chips/cracks [list]  \n4. Headlights, taillights, indicators, brake lights operation [list]  \n5. Exterior trim, weather stripping condition [list]  \n6. Underbody sagging or leaks [longText]  \n\n## Interior & Comfort\n1. Seat upholstery wear and adjustment [list]  \n2. Seat belt function and pretensioners [list]  \n3. Dashboard indicator lights operation [list]  \n4. HVAC performance (heat, A/C, blower speeds) [list]  \n5. Check sunroof/moonroof operation (if equipped) [list]  \n6. Interior lights, courtesy lamps, mirror operation [list]  \n\n## Electrical & Electronics\n1. Battery health (voltage) and age [number]  \n2. Alternator output voltage under load [number]  \n3. Central locking, power windows, mirrors [list]  \n4. Audio/video system and speakers [list]  \n5. Instrument cluster gauges accuracy [list]  \n6. OBD-II scan: presence of DTC codes [textAnswer]  \n7. Fuse box and relays corrosion or damage [list]  \n\n## Underbody & Exhaust\n1. Exhaust system (muffler, pipes) rust or leaks [list]  \n2. Catalytic converter condition [list]  \n3. Fuel tank and lines corrosion/leaks [list]  \n4. Inspect chassis rails and crossmembers for rust [list]  \n5. Inspect brake and fuel line routing/clamps [list]  \n\n## Safety & Miscellaneous\n1. Airbag warning light status [list]  \n2. Horn, alarms, immobilizer operation [list]  \n3. Check jack, lug wrench, tool kit presence [list]  \n4. First aid kit, fire extinguisher present [list]  \n5. Owner\u2019s manual, service records availability [list]  \n6. Overall vehicle condition rating [slider]  \n\nPlease review and let me know if this covers everything or if you\u2019d like to add, remove, or adjust any items. When you\u2019re happy with it, just say \u201cgenerate\u201d (or similar) and I\u2019ll create the final checklist.", "reasoning_content": "\nI need to draft a comprehensive pre-purchase checklist for a 2012 Daewoo Lacetti. I\u2019ll cover every major system\u2014engine, transmission, brakes, suspension, body, interior, electrical, tires, underbody, safety. For each item, I\u2019ll assign appropriate input types ([list], [number], [textAnswer], [longText], [slider]). Then I\u2019ll present the full draft and ask the user to confirm before generating.\n"}

